Alternative forms[edit]

  • Fussball (Switzerland, Liechtenstein, Luxembourg)

Etymology[edit]

From Fuß (“foot”) +‎ Ball (“ball”), a calque of English football. Compare the borrowing Football (“American football”).

Pronunciation[edit]

  • IPA(key): /ˈfuːsˌbal/
  • audio
    		(file)

Noun[edit]

Fußball m (genitive Fußballs or Fußballes, plural Fußbälle)

  1. the sport of association football; soccer
  2. the ball with which association football is played: a football, a soccer ball
